The upper limit in my example is 10. Once the odd thread prints 9 or the even thread prints 10, then we don&#39;t need any of the threads to wait any more. So, we can handle that using one `if-block`. Or, we can use the overloaded `wait(long timeout)` method for the wait to be timed out.
One flaw here though. With this code, we cannot guarantee which thread will start execution first.

